                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51637/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-17T23:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1923—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 18—2:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. Reference to your number 33, April 17, 4 p.m. Department will of course have
                    in mind its number 159 of September 29, 1921, 6 p.m.,<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d691fn33">Not printed.</note> transmitting designation by New York
                    Federal Reserve Bank of the National City Bank as its Cuban agent under section
                    14, Federal Reserve Act. I understand however that this agency has not actively
                    engaged in the transaction of business prescribed in that section. Believe
                    conditions favorable to the success of an agency which will engage actively in
                    the transaction of such business and that opportune announcement that one will
                    be established will be helpful in the present crisis.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
